Qwen3.6 ModelOpt mixed NVFP4 support — upstream PR #27906.

Source: https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/pull/27906
  "[Model] Support Qwen3.6 ModelOpt mixed NVFP4" (sgl-project:mmangkad/...; closes #26967)
  Captured 2026-06-24 via `curl .../pull/27906.diff`. PR state at capture: OPEN,
  CI unstable, NOT merged. Base is post-v0.5.13 main.
  REGENERATE from the merged commit once it lands, then DROP this patch when a
  release tag containing it is used (gate: recipe APPLY_QWEN36_MIXED_NVFP4_PR27906).

Target model: nvidia/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-NVFP4 — a modelopt MIXED_PRECISION checkpoint
  (W4A16_NVFP4 MoE experts + shared-expert linears + lm_head, FP8 attention/linear_attn,
  FP8 KV cache, MTP excluded). Arch Qwen3_5MoeForConditionalGeneration (weights under
  model.language_model.*). Stock v0.5.13 cannot load it (see model profile header).

What it does (8 hunked files; the test file from the PR is intentionally NOT included):
  - configs/model_config.py: detect MIXED_PRECISION with real NVFP4 / W4A16_NVFP4 layer
    entries → route to modelopt_mixed (not the w4afp8 fallback); read hf_quant_config.json
    for KV-cache metadata missing from config.json. (Supersedes our runtime
    _sgl_mixed_nvfp4_dispatch_ patch.)
  - layers/quantization/modelopt_quant.py: ModelOptMixedPrecisionConfig now resolves
    quantized-layer names across model.language_model.* / language_model.model.* wrapper
    prefixes and lm_head; adds a dedicated ModelOptNvFp4A16LinearMethod (NVFP4 weight-only
    / W4A16, Marlin, group_size=16) and routes W4A16_NVFP4 Linear/LMHead/MoE to it.
    (Supersedes our runtime _sgl_mixed_nvfp4_variant_ patch AND adds lm_head + W4A16
    handling our narrow patches lacked.)
  - layers/logits_processor.py + layers/vocab_parallel_embedding.py: quantized lm_head
    (ParallelLMHead) support.
  - model_loader/weight_utils.py: weight-name mapping for the wrapper prefixes.
  - models/qwen3_5_mtp.py + speculative/eagle_worker_v2.py: MTP / NEXTN path for this
    checkpoint (the profile uses speculative_algo: NEXTN).

REBASE NOTES (PR base = post-v0.5.13 main; this is rebased onto tag v0.5.13):
  Applies clean with `git apply` (strict, fuzz=0) against v0.5.13 as captured here.
  One PR change was DROPPED during rebase because it targets a main-only feature absent
  in v0.5.13: the `use_per_token_activation` constructor param/attribute on
  ModelOptFp4Config (and the `nvfp4a16_config = ModelOptFp4Config(..., use_per_token_
  activation=False)` kwarg). v0.5.13's NVFP4 `apply` controls per-token activation via the
  env var SGLANG_FLASHINFER_NVFP4_PER_TOKEN_ACTIVATION (default off = per-tensor), and the
  new ModelOptNvFp4A16LinearMethod does NOT read that attribute (Marlin weight-only path),
  so on v0.5.13 nvfp4a16_config == nvfp4_config and W4A16 activations stay per-tensor —
  functionally equivalent to the PR's intent. If you re-capture against a newer base that
  HAS the param, restore the kwarg + the __init__ refinement (PR hunk @@ -1200/-1263).
  If the in-container dry-run fails on a future v0.5.13 point bump, regenerate from the PR.

